  "prompt": "When is the best marriage age for a girl?",
  "response": "The best marriage age for a girl can vary significantly depending on cultural, societal, personal, and individual factors. There is no universally \"best\" age, as it depends on personal readiness, life circumstances, career goals, educational attainment, emotional maturity, and the desires of the individual.\n\nIn many cultures, people might suggest an age range from the late twenties to early thirties as an optimal time for marriage. This is often considered a time when individuals are likely to have completed their education, established their careers, and gained sufficient life experience and emotional maturity to handle the responsibilities of marriage.\n\nHowever, it's important to recognize that the best age to get married is highly individual. Each person should consider their own personal circumstances, life goals, and readiness for the commitment of marriage rather than conforming to societal expectations. There is no rush, and taking the time to ensure that the decision to marry aligns with one's own values and circumstances is crucial.",
